      • makeLists

        public void makeLists(java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> nodeAttributeKeys,
                      java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> edgeAttributeKeys,
                      java.util.ArrayList<java.lang.String> layoutAttributeKeys)
        Creates two ContorlP5.Group, one for nodes and one for edges. Both groups are attached to an instance of ControlP5 that draws them in the PApplet using an internal ControlP5.autoDraw() method. It initializes the ControlP5 variables every time it is invoked. Albeit is is done in the constructor, it is necessary to do it here in order to have fresh variables every time the user loads new files without restarting the application
        Parameters:
        nodeAttributeKeys - The list of node attributes retrieved from the graphml header
        edgeAttributeKeys - The list of edge attributes retrieved from the graphml header
